video.title: Little Einsteins
video.synopsis: Leo, June, Quincy and Annie blast off in their versatile ship, Rocket, for unforgettable musical and artistic adventures all over the world.

episodes.synopsis: As June star-gazes and admires Saturn, one of its rings falls off and lands in her yard, so the gang embarks on a mission through space to return it.
episodes.title: Ring Around the Planet

episodes.synopsis: The Little Einsteins spot a bald eagle picking up sticks, but the bird mistakenly takes Leo's baton, and the team must find a way to get it back.
episodes.title: I Love to Conduct

episodes.synopsis: When Rocket gets nervous about competing with Big Jet, he gets a case of the hiccups, and the team must help him cure it before a big race.
episodes.title: Hungarian Hiccups

episodes.synopsis: When Rocket needs help finding Little Whale, the new friend he met at the beach, the team ventures underwater so they can see the whale's world.
episodes.title: Whale Tale

episodes.synopsis: The team hears music coming from a piece of paper, which is actually a treasure map, leading them on a pirate adventure and a race against Big Jet.
episodes.title: Pirate's Treasure

episodes.synopsis: When a strong gust of wind blows away the balloons for Annie's birthday party, her friends must find them and bring them back in time to celebrate.
episodes.title: The Birthday Balloons

episodes.synopsis: In Egypt, the team discovers hieroglyphics, the Great Sphinx and a harp with such golden tones it can open a pyramid that has been locked for ages.
episodes.title: The Legend of the Golden Pyramid

episodes.synopsis: The Little Einsteins travel to China to help a little dragon kite find her friends and face her fears in time for a kite parade along the Great Wall.
episodes.title: Dragon Kite

episodes.synopsis: The team help their friend, Little Red Train, reclaim a party bag in the Wild West, while Rocket has a face-off with Big Jet, who stole the loot.
episodes.title: Go West, Young Train

episodes.synopsis: The Einsteins visit the Three Little Pigs on their farm and discover mysterious seeds. They help the piggies grow them so they can see what sprouts.
episodes.title: Farmer Annie

episodes.synopsis: On Halloween, Rocket and the team go trick-or-treating, but as they fill their pumpkins with treats, they find they are being chased by hungry ghosts.
episodes.title: A Little Einsteins Halloween

episodes.synopsis: When Leo, June and Quincy blow musical bubbles, they get trapped in a super bubble that whisks them across the ocean, and only Annie can save them.
episodes.title: Annie's Solo Mission

episodes.synopsis: When the team meets a tiny mouse who has a present for the moon, they take him on a trip to the great Matterhorn to help him offer his special gift.
episodes.title: The Mouse and the Moon

episodes.synopsis: The team finds out that a good knight has been locked up inside a castle by a bad knight, so they search for the musical key that will set him free.
episodes.title: The Good Knight and the Bad Knight

episodes.synopsis: When Santa drops Annie's Christmas present -- a wish box -- in the snowy Himalayan mountains, the team hikes up Mount Everest to find it.
episodes.title: The Christmas Wish

episodes.synopsis: Leo and the team recount how they became The Little Einsteins by finding a place for Rocket to live so that he could be with the rest of the group.
episodes.title: How We Became the Little Einsteins: The True Story

episodes.synopsis: The team goes to Australia, where they help their baby kangaroo friend Joey get ready for an animal talent show in the Sydney Opera House.
episodes.title: Jump for Joey

episodes.synopsis: When the team searches for a baby reindeer, they get help from the northern lights, as the aurora borealis lights their path through the cold night.
episodes.title: The Northern Night Light

episodes.synopsis: The team goes to the Netherlands to help a flower named Baby Tulip. It is time for him to bloom, but Big Jet is trying to stop him.
episodes.title: O Yes, O Yes, It's Springtime!

episodes.synopsis: The team travels to Alaska, where they go exploring in a forest filled with totem poles and discover a little totem pole who wants to be big.
episodes.title: A Tall Totem Tale

episodes.synopsis: The team is thrilled to find a Big-and-Small machine, but when it breaks, it shrinks the kids and Rocket, who must find a way back to normal size.
episodes.title: The Incredible Shrinking Adventure

episodes.synopsis: When a newly hatched duck mistakes June for his mother and follows her, the team helps the baby learn to fly and find his real mom and seven siblings.
episodes.title: Duck, Duck, June

episodes.synopsis: In Africa, Rocket gets stuck in a waterfall trying to protect the wildebeests, so the gang goes on safari to find animals that can help save him.
episodes.title: Rocket Safari

episodes.synopsis: In the Big Woods of Arkansas, the team discovers an ivory-billed woodpecker and tries to help him find another woodpecker far away on a mountaintop.
episodes.title: Knock on Wood

episodes.synopsis: When the team has a sleepover and bedtime arrives, they notice that Rocket cannot fall asleep and needs them to show him a method for nodding off.
episodes.title: A Galactic Goodnight

episodes.synopsis: While the team cleans the Rocket room, they find intriguing blueprints and try to build a machine that will make today everyone's birthday.
episodes.title: The Birthday Machine

episodes.synopsis: Annie befriends an adorable little caterpillar who lives in the middle of one of Van Gogh's paintings and helps him get to a special tree.
episodes.title: A Brand New Outfit

episodes.synopsis: The team returns to the musical Tree of Many Colors to visit their friend, Butterfly, and help him find his invitation to the family migration party.
episodes.title: The Missing Invitation

episodes.synopsis: When Rocket's anchor gets stuck on a rock in the rising Arabian Sea, Quincy must use magical instruments to save him before the team gets seasick.
episodes.title: Quincy and the Magic Instruments

episodes.synopsis: Annie and Leo enter the fairy tale "Hansel and Gretel," leaving a trail of musical notes, finding tempting sweets and rescuing two kids from a witch.
episodes.title: Brothers and Sisters to the Rescue!

episodes.synopsis: The gang tries to get June to a ball before midnight so she can try on a glass slipper -- and teaches Rocket to dance along the way.
episodes.title: The Glass Slipper Ball

episodes.synopsis: The team goes under the sea to bring two lonely hermit crabs back together, who sing a special song about friendship that makes everyone happy.
episodes.title: Annie's Love Song

episodes.synopsis: The team hurries to Paris to get a ticket for a musical pet who needs one to board a special train before it leaves the station.
episodes.title: Melody, the Music Pet

episodes.synopsis: June and the team go to Prague, where they help three lost puppets make it to the theater in time to perform their puppet show.
episodes.title: The Puppet Princess

episodes.synopsis: When Rocket's fuel tanks hover near empty, he finds an energy-boosting and tuneful remedy filling up at the musical gas station.
episodes.title: Super Fast!

episodes.synopsis: The team is on safari when they find a baby chimp singing a sad song. Luckily Annie understands music, so they can help him find his parents.
episodes.title: He Speaks Music!

episodes.synopsis: The team sees a family of baby cellos hatching from their cases and learns about the instrument as they help one baby find his mother.
episodes.title: Hello Cello!

episodes.synopsis: The higher Annie sings, the higher her toy plane flies, which comes in handy when she must help rescue a helicopter stuck atop a giant redwood tree.
episodes.title: Annie and the Little Toy Plane

episodes.synopsis: The team goes to the Grand Prix in Monaco, where they try to help a fast car made of musical instruments pass the bigger cars and win the race.
episodes.title: Carmine's Big Race

episodes.synopsis: As all the best flying machines gather to compete, Big Jet messes with Rocket's flying buttons as revenge for beating him in the last Great Sky Race.
episodes.title: The Great Sky Race Rematch

episodes.synopsis: Quincy's beloved fairy tale echoes "Sleeping Beauty," as the team must wake a princess bassoon from a sleeping spell so she can play her happy tune.
episodes.title: Sleeping Bassoon

episodes.synopsis: The Little Einsteins gather three ingredients to make their hungry friend Rocket his favorite food -- Rocket soup -- and restore his fading energy.
episodes.title: Rocket Soup

episodes.synopsis: June's dance students are four blue-footed booby birds. The team helps a baby booby who wants to dance with the big birds in the ballet recital.
episodes.title: The Blue Footed Booby Bird Ballet

episodes.synopsis: Rocket's story mirrors "Little Red Riding Hood" as he brings rocket soup to the ailing Grandma Rocket, but Big Jet steals it and eats it all up.
episodes.title: Little Red Rockethood

episodes.synopsis: In Egypt, the team meets the Great Sphinx and helps him obtain the three missing pieces of a puzzle in time to make sure its magic does not slip away.
episodes.title: The Puzzle of the Sphinx

episodes.synopsis: During migration season, a cute baby goose follows Rocket instead of his flock, and the team must help the little creature get back on track.
episodes.title: The Wild Goose Chase

episodes.synopsis: The team tells a story about a golden goose who has a beautiful voice, but when a giant seizes the creature, they must find a way to set it free.
episodes.title: Annie and the Beanstalk

episodes.synopsis: In Iceland, June performs a ballet about a toy prince who brings joy to all the toys in his kingdom, but needs a little help from June.
episodes.title: The Wind-Up Toy Prince

episodes.synopsis: When a train full of ice cream breaks down, the team meets the driver, Mr. Penguin, and helps him deliver the ice cream before it melts in the sun.
episodes.title: Mr. Penguin's Ice Cream Adventure

episodes.synopsis: Annie has a big performance coming up, but she can't find her music. Her friends try to help her show start on the right note.
episodes.title: Annie, Get Your Microphone

episodes.synopsis: While digging in his garden, Rocket finds a treasure map that leads to a fortune, but when Big Jet steals the map, the race for the treasure is on.
episodes.title: The Treasure Behind the Little Red Door

episodes.synopsis: The Little Einsteins must find a golden music key that unlocks a secret prize box, but they will have to beat Big Jet, who wants to get it first.
episodes.title: The Secret Mystery Prize

episodes.synopsis: In Africa, Rocket plays with the baby animals and transforms himself into a giraffe, monkey and elephant. He feeds his new friends snacks.
episodes.title: Animal Snack Time

episodes.synopsis: Annie wants to win a beautiful stuffed horse at a carnival, which means the team must find three musical clues to a guessing game in the nick of time.
episodes.title: The Great Schubert's Guessing Game

episodes.synopsis: When the team happens upon a baby piccolodactyl who hides from a loud sound, they must find and rescue him before a volcano erupts.
episodes.title: Quincy and the Instrument Dinosaurs

episodes.synopsis: Rocket and the team want to help build a house for the Three Little Pigs, but the huffing and puffing Big Bad Wolf has other ideas.
episodes.title: Build It Rocket!

episodes.synopsis: Leo has a party for his music pet and takes her on a hot air balloon ride. When a big gust of wind blows them into danger, the team must help.
episodes.title: Melody and Me

episodes.synopsis: The team goes to Scotland to free some music monsters from the Loch Ness monster's cage so they can sing, play, be happy and bring joy again.
episodes.title: Music Monsters

episodes.synopsis: The team visits a museum in France, where they must free a unicorn from a curse so he can conduct music and help all the animals sing together.
episodes.title: The Song of the Unicorn

episodes.synopsis: The team goes to the Arctic, where the local wild creatures help them save the instrument fairies, who create the beautiful, colorful aurora borealis.
episodes.title: Flight of the Instrument Fairies

episodes.synopsis: Leo's Silly Sock longs to join the rest of the wardrobe at the Silly Clothes Circus in Paris -- if the team can just get him there in time.
episodes.title: Silly Sock Saves the Circus

episodes.synopsis: What happens when a king loses his precious musical treasure? He needs the help of the Little Einsteins to retrieve it, of course.
episodes.title: Go Team!

episodes.synopsis: June and the team help a music robot find his missing batteries so he can return to space and fly back to his home planet.
episodes.title: The Music Robot from Outer Space

episodes.synopsis: The team blasts off to Mexico to find Big Jet and take back the special items he stole from them that they want to bring to school for show-and-tell.
episodes.title: Show and Tell

episodes.synopsis: When the Big Bad Wolf sneezes away a house that Rocket gave three baby bugs for shelter, the team must get the house back before a big rain comes.
episodes.title: Rocket the Bug

episodes.synopsis: The Little Einsteins bravely put themselves in the path of danger when they spot smoke billowing from the mouth of a volcano.
episodes.title: Fire Truck Rocket!

episodes.synopsis: The team goes to India for the elephant festival. Leo wins an egg with a tiny elephant inside who needs the team to feed her peanuts.
episodes.title: Little Elephant's Big Parade!
